page.title: 16FLORA AND FAUNA
page.content: Comfrey,Sweet Cicily and Butter-Bur are seen growing in Mount Eff Lane. Comfrey is a plant.It can be used for healing and can be made into medicine. Comfrey can also be eaten.The Sweet Cicily in our area is found growing by the Tees.Also seen are Dandilions, Hedge Garlic,Buttercups,Meadow Safifruge and Celandines.We also found a Puffball fungus.There is little plant life in the{Tees}apart from Water Moss. {Mink}are frequently seen in our area and have become firmly established by{Abbey Bridge}map reference 147,065.
